{"CALUMBA":[{"def":"The root of a plant (Jateorrhiza Calumba, and probably Cocculus palmatus), indigenous in Mozambique.","pos":""}],"CALUMBIN":[{"def":"A bitter principle extracted as a white crystalline substance from the calumba root.","pos":""}],"CALUMET":[{"def":"A kind of pipe, used by the North American Indians for smoking tobacco.","pos":""}],"CALUMNIATE":[{"def":"To accuse falsely and maliciously of a crime or offense, or of something disreputable; to slander; to libel.","pos":""}],"CALUMNIATION":[{"def":"False accusation of crime or offense, or a malicious and false representation of the words or actions of another, with a view to injure his good name.","pos":""}],"CALUMNIATOR":[{"def":"One who calumniates.","pos":""}],"CALUMNIATORY":[{"def":"Containing calumny; slanderous.","pos":""}],"CALUMNIOUS":[{"def":"Containing or implying calumny; false, malicious, and injurious to reputation; slanderous; as, calumnious reports.","pos":""}],"CALUMNY":[{"def":"False accusation of a crime or offense, maliciously made or reported, to the injury of another; malicious misrepresentation; slander; detraction.","pos":""}]}